From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: at-xx-frida <noreply@local>
Date: Thu, 22 May 2026 00:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] relax payload-base library check to executable-only

On Android 10+ many system .so files (notably /system/lib64/libstagefright.so)
are mapped as PROT_EXEC only (--xp) with a separate PROT_READ segment (r--p),
not the legacy r-xp. The original `m.readable && m.executable` check excluded
the --xp segment, so `do_prepare_zymbiote_injection` could not anchor a payload
base and `frida -f` failed with "Unable to pick a payload base".

Drop the readable requirement and synthesize payload_original_protection from
actual mapping flags so the page can be restored to its original perms after
the agent detaches.

---
 src/linux/linux-host-session.vala | 6 ++++--
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/linux/linux-host-session.vala b/src/linux/linux-host-session.vala
--- a/src/linux/linux-host-session.vala
+++ b/src/linux/linux-host-session.vala
@@ -1709,9 +1709,11 @@ namespace Frida {

 			foreach (var m in maps) {
 				unowned string path = m.path;
-				if (path.has_suffix ("/libstagefright.so") && m.readable && m.executable) {
+				if (path.has_suffix ("/libstagefright.so") && m.executable) {
 					if (payload_base == 0) {
 						payload_base = m.end - Gum.query_page_size ();
-						payload_original_protection = Posix.PROT_READ | Posix.PROT_EXEC;
+						payload_original_protection = Posix.PROT_EXEC;
+						if (m.readable)
+							payload_original_protection |= Posix.PROT_READ;
 						if (m.writable)
 							payload_original_protection |= Posix.PROT_WRITE;
--
